Instructions

 

Please read the following instructions carefully.



For this survey, you will hear a pair of audio files named A and B. You should press the play button ▶️ to hear the audio. For each pair, you will answer a single question, which audio file you prefer regarding sound quality.

 


You can score your preference by any number between -3 and 3. Here, the preference score refers to,


	-3 = Strongly prefer A (SP-A),
	-2 = Moderately prefer A (MP-A),
	-1 = Slightly prefer A (SLP-A),
	0 = No preference (NP),
	1 = Slightly prefer B (SLP-B),
	2 = Moderately prefer B (MP-B),
	3 = Strongly prefer B (SP-B)


If both audio signals are of the same sound quality, you should score as 0. If you prefer A, your preference score should be nearer to -3. Similarly, if you prefer B more, your score should be more close to 3. However, you can give a score to a single decimal number, for example, 1.6 can be given as a score.



How to answer a question:


	Listen to audio signal, A.
	Listen to audio signal, B.
	Move the slider to give your preference score.
	The NEXT button will appear on the right bottom side of the page.
	Click the NEXT button to answer the next question.
